title: The Rock answer questions about his phone stunt after RAW taping | GiveMeSport
text:
The Rock answer questions about his phone stunt after RAW taping Published 24/7 
Dwyane Johnson is busy tearing up Hollywood at the moment, but the last time he appeared in a WWE ring was at WrestleMania 32 last April. 
He made an appearance at this week’s RAW taping from the Staples Center to film a scene for a movie he is producing based on the life and career of WWE wrestler Paige. 
This particular scene from “Fighting With My Family” included a recreation of Paige winning the WWE Divas Championship from AJ Lee in 2014. Article continues below 
The Rock decided to add a little excitement for the fans as he called CM Punk, Lee’s husband, in the ring after the arena began to chant the former WWE superstars name upon hearing Lee announced. 
Johnson’s attempt was for naught as his former opponent’s phone went straight to voicemail. He even tried FaceTiming him, but didn’t have any luck with that either. Article continues below
